“I am required by statute to appoint a mayoral committee (mayco) to assist me in the governance of the city, and I am ready to do so,” he said yesterday. “As was known, last week former mayor Patricia de Lille applied urgently to the High Court in Cape Town for an interim order reinstating her membership of the Democratic Alliance and as mayor pending the determination of an application by her for final relief against the DA, which would be heard on May 25. “At the completion of the court proceedings on Friday evening in the urgent application, the court reserved judgment and said it was not in a position to indicate when its ruling would be delivered. “I am advised that, legally,
nothing precludes me from proceeding with the appointment of a mayco, but out of respect to the court I
will delay making the appointment until 3pm on Monday, 14 May 2018, (today). - African News Agency (ANA)